http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/Pearls-Group-chairman-in-judicial-custody/article14018606.ece

A Delhi court on Saturday remanded Pearls Group chairman-cum-managing director Nirmal Singh Bhangoo and three others to judicial custody in connection with the alleged swindling of about Rs. 45,000 crore from more than five crore investors.Chief Metropolitan Magistrate Sugandha Aggarwal sent Bhangoo, Sukhdev Singh, managing director and promoter-director of Pearls Agrotech Corporation Ltd., Gurmeet Singh, executive director (Finance) and Subrata Bhattacharya, executive director in Pearls Golden Forest Ltd. and Pearls Agrotech Corporation Ltd to judicial custody till February 6.Earlier, the CBI had produced all the accused before the court on completion of police custody.“Today accused persons have been produced in court after 14-day police custody remand. Now an application has been moved seeking 14-day judicial custody. For the reasons stated in the application, the same is allowed,’’ the court said.The Maharashtra Police, meanwhile, have moved an application seeking Bhangoo’s custody in another case.The court will take up the application on Monday.The CBI had arrested the four accused on January 15 for allegedly collecting money from investors in Delhi, Punjab, Haryana, Rajasthan and other States through Pearls Agrotech Corporation Ltd. and Pearls Golden Forest Ltd. on the pretext of allotting land to them.